  "text": "The DPPH-assay was performed as previously described [CITATION_1] . Different volumes (10-100 µL) of samples, dissolved in methanol, were mixed with 90 µM DPPH solution (1 mL) and made up with 95% methanol to a final volume (4 mL). After 30 min at room temperature, absorbance of the resulting solutions and the control (same chemicals without sample) were measured spectrophotometrically at 515 nm. Methanol was used as a blank. For each sample, the experiment was performed in triplicate. Radical scavenging capacity (RSC), expressed as percentage, was calculated by the following equation:",
